Hi,
Right now, it's not easy to get various drawing profiling info(shader switches, draw calls, texture bindings, etc). It could be done following way:
a) Add class ProfilingInfo:

``` csharp
  public sealed class ProfilingInfo
  {
    public int TextureBindings { get; set; }
    public int DrawCalls { get; set; }
    public int ShaderSwitches { get; set; }
    public int VertexCount { get; set; }
  }
```

b) Add readonly property ProfilingInfo to the GraphicsDevice class and make it updated during the rendering.

c) Then in the runtime it could used following way:

``` csharp
  protected override void Draw(GameTime gameTime)
  {
    GraphicsDevice.ProfilingInfo.Reset();
    ...
    // Render
    ...
    // GraphicsDevice.ProfilingInfo holds the required info for the rendered frame
  }
```
